---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import DevBanner from '../components/DevBanner.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Terms of service — Peg">
  <DevBanner message="MOCKUP." />
  <Header />

  <div class="container-narrow form-page legal-page">
    <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
    <h1 style="font-size:28px; margin-bottom:20px;">Terms of Service</h1>

    <div class="legal-page-note">
      This is placeholder text for a working mockup, not a real terms of service. It needs to be reviewed..
    </div>

    <h2>Using ZENZKO.com</h2>
    <p>Zenzko lets you publish a page for one product and take payment for it. Free-plan stores are locked once published; upgrading unlocks editing for that store.</p>

    <h2>Your store is yours</h2>
    <p>You're responsible for what you list — that it's accurately described, legal to sell, and yours to sell. We don't review listings before they go live.</p>

    <h2>Fees</h2>
    <p>We take a percentage of each sale as a platform fee. The current rate is shown on the homepage. There's no fee for creating or publishing a store — only on completed sales.</p>

    <h2>Payments and Stripe Connect</h2>
    <p>Payments run through Stripe Connect Standard accounts. You have your own direct relationship with Stripe, separate from us — refunds, chargebacks, and disputes are between you and Stripe. See our <a href="/disputes">Disputes</a> page for more detail.</p>

    <h2>Prohibited items</h2>
    <p>You can't list anything illegal, counterfeit, or restricted under Stripe's own terms. We can take down listings that break this without notice.</p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>We may update these terms from time to time. Continued use of Zenzko after a change means you accept the update.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions can go to <a href="mailto:hello@peg.store">hello@zenzko.com</a> (placeholder address).</p>
  </div>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
